{
  "text": "In a stunning turn of events, the attack that killed Iran's Supreme Leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei happened in the middle of the morning, catching the regime off guard. This wasn't a random strike; it was the result of months of planning. President Trump noted that Khamenei was unable to avoid our intelligence and highly sophisticated tracking systems, which allowed the US and Israel to pinpoint his exact location. By monitoring the movements of bodyguards and officials, intelligence agencies were able to build up a pattern of life to predict and understand activity, waiting for that perfect moment of vulnerability. There was a clear division of labor during the mission, with Israel focusing on strikes to hit leadership targets while the US handled military objectives. When the window of opportunity opened, Israeli jets launched a massive assault. Reports indicate that they used 30 bombs to attack the compound around 09:40 local time, aiming for an underground bunker. The strike was devastating. Three senior Iranian defence officials have been confirmed dead by Iran, including the Defence Council secretary and the IRGC commander. While this is a massive blow, the future remains uncertain. Iran had been prepared for this possibility though, with reports that the plans for succession had already been put in place for its top leadership.",
